description: TEHRAN – Persepolis football team provisionally climbed to the top of the Iran’s Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) after beating Havadar 2-0 on Saturday.
title: PGPL: Persepolis beat Havadar to move top

description: TEHRAN- Bolivia’s Ambassador to Iran Romina Guadalupe Perez Ramos has noted that the world should be aware of peacefulness of Iran’s nuclear program.
title: Intl. community must recognize civilian nature of Iran nuclear program, Bolivian envoy says

description: TEHRAN- The Canadian House of Commons passed a motion adding the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) to an official list of "terrorist organizations," which was sharply denounced by the Iranian Foreign Ministry.
title: Iran slams Canada move against IRGC

description: TEHRAN - Iran's Deputy Ambassador to Kabul, Hassan Mortazavi, highlighted Iran's commitment to serving as a dependable energy supplier to Afghanistan during a meeting with Abdul Latif Mansoor, the Acting Minister of Water and Energy of Afghanistan's caretaker government in Kabul.
title: Iran can ensure stable energy supply to Afghanistan: deputy ambassador

description: TEHRAN – Iran had practiced its April attack on Israeli positions in the occupied territories multiple times during military maneuvers, said the spokesman for the Islamic Revolution Guard corps on Saturday.
title: Iran had previously practiced April attack on occupied territories: IRGC

description: TEHRAN- The representative of the Kurdistan Region of Iraq to Iran has said that given the positive achievements of Nechirvan Barzani’s visit to Tehran, the autonomous region will definitely witness the development of political, security, and economic cooperation between Iran and the Kurdistan Region in the future.
title: Iraqi Kurdistan seeking to prevent past issues from straining relations with Iran: KRG rep.

description: TEHRAN- Iran’s UN envoy has reaffirmed Tehran’s unwavering support for Palestine’s full UN membership, calling it a critical first step in redressing the historical injustices suffered by the Palestinian people.
title: Iran supports full UN membership for Palestine

description: TEHRAN - In a note, Kayhan discussed the report of the old American magazine Nation about Iran's missile attack on Israel and wrote: This magazine believes that Iran was the winner of the recent war with Israel.
title: Iran's successful operation made Israel regret its action

description: TEHRAN - In a session held in Tehran on Saturday, Palestinian author Munir Shafiq took the lead in a discussion centered on "Palestine, Resistance, and Media," accompanied by a panel of analysts.
title: Munir Shafiq: Resistance led Palestinians into total victory

description: TEHRAN-The play “Misery” directed by Pouya Saeidi will be performed at Iranshahr Theater in Tehran from May 14.
title: Adaptation of Stephen Belber’s “Tape” to be staged at Iranshahr Theater

description: TEHRAN-The 35th Tehran International Book Fair (TIBF) is underway in Tehran’s Imam Khomeini Mosalla (prayer grounds), bringing together over 2,700 local and 60 foreign publishers from 25 countries attending the event.
title: Foreign attendees hail magnificence of Tehran International Book Fair

description: TEHRAN - In a meeting with Iraqi Kurdistan Region President Nechervan Barzani, Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyed Ali Khamenei emphasized the close bonds between Iran and the Kurdish communities outside the country.
title: 'Kurds are one of us': Leader

description: TEHRAN - The Israeli ambassador’s shredding of the United Nations Charter while standing in anger at the UN podium reflects how Tel Aviv views the world’s most important international organization.
title: Israeli envoy's paper shredder publicity stunt falls flat

description: TEHRAN- The adoption of a resolution by the United Nations General Assembly that overwhelmingly backed the Palestinian bid for full UN membership has highlighted growing global solidarity with Palestinians in the wake of Israel’s brutal war on the Gaza Strip.
title: Historic vote for Palestine

description: At least 50 professors have been arrested at pro-Palestinian campus demonstrations across the US, according to US broadcaster CNN, which said it reviewed police records, court filings and news reports.
title: At least 50 professors arrested at US campus protests: CNN

description: TEHRAN - Key talks between the cultural coordination center of the Asia Cooperation Dialogue and the Touring & Automobile Club of Iran have highlighted a push for a women’s tourism rally as an international collaboration.
title: TACI, ACD unite for women's tourism rally

description: TEHRAN – As the countdown to the Kish International Tourism Exhibition has started, some Iranian chefs are invited to participate to enrich the event.
title: Chefs de cuisine to convene at Kish expo

description: TEHRAN – On May 10, an exhibition of handicrafts made by Zoroastrian artisans was held in the UNESCO-listed city of Yazd in the heart of Iran.
title: Exhibit highlights Zoroastrian’s cultural contribution

description: TEHRAN - In a race against time to preserve archaeological heritage, an emergency excavation has unearthed a burial site at Ultan Qalasi in Ardabil province, revealing artifacts dating back to the Iron Age.
title: Ultan Qalasi: salvage work unveils ancient burial site in Ardabil province

description: TEHRAN – 170 Indonesian tourists arrived in Iran’s Khuzestan on Saturday to explore the provincial touristic attractions and economic capacities.
title: Khuzestan enraptures tens of Indonesian tourists

description: TEHRAN – A team of archaeologists has embarked on a groundbreaking excavation project at Falak ol-Aflak hill, the site of the famed Sassanid-era fortress in Lorestan province.
title: Excavations unearth ancient layers of history at Falak ol-Aflak hill

description: TEHRAN – Iran junior volleyball team defeated Turkmenistan 3-2 (23-25, 21-15, 25-16, 25-23, 19-17) at the Central Asian Volleyball Association (CAVA) Nation’s Volleyball League.
title: Iran start CAVA Nation’s Volleyball League on high

description: TEHRAN – Sobhan Ahmadi and Mehdi Pirjahan of Iran won a gold and silver medal at the 2024 Diamond League in Doha, Qatar.
title: Diamond League: Iranian athletes win medals in Doha

description: TEHRAN - The Internet-based digital revolution is racing ahead like a runaway train, leaving policymakers in its dust or even less. In the fast lane, countries are struggling to keep up with the lightning-fast evolution of, now ubiquitous, AI-powered products. But one country, Iran, is stuck in neutral; its “National Network of Information” policy mired in misunderstanding and ambiguity. It's a tale of missed opportunities, as the government fails to catch the digital wave, instead finding itself swept away by the tide of technological advancements. Will the Iranian government be able to reverse gear and get back on track, or will it be forever left in the slow lane, watching as other countries zoom past, leaving it in their dust?
title: A nation of networks: Iran’s NIN unmasked

description: TEHRAN –Two years after the enactment of the law on supporting families and the youth, investigations have shown that the health ministry has played a central role in the implementation of the law, Hasan Farshidi, an official with the health ministry, has said.
title: Health ministry plays key role in youth law enforcement

description: TEHRAN –Iran is the most important country in West Asia in terms of housing migratory birds in winter as around two million birds fly each year to spend winter in the country's wetlands, according to an official with the Department of Environment (DOE).
title: Iran is main wintering habitat in West Asia for migratory birds: official

description: TEHRAN – The United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime (UNODC) and the Iranian law enforcement force have explored ways to boost cooperation in areas related to drug trafficking and drug-related crimes.
title: UNODC, Iran discuss enhanced cooperation on drug-related crimes

description: TEHRAN – Head coach of Iran’s women’s futsal team Forouzan Soleymani said that they need a long-term plan to move further in the FIFA World Ranking.
title: Iran’s women’s futsal need long-term plan: Soleymani

description: BEIJING- A group of journalists from the Asian, African, and Pacific countries visited the largest exhibition hall of China’s giant technology company Huawei in Beijing.
title: Asian, African, Pacific media visit Huawei exhibition hall in Beijing

description: TEHRAN – Head of Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines, and Agriculture (ICCIMA) Samad Hassanzadeh has stressed that the private sectors of Iran and South Korea can help give a boost to trade ties between the two countries.
title: Iran, South Korea private sectors urged to help expand bilateral trade

description: TEHRAN - Managing Director of the Pars Oil and Gas Company (POGC) Mohammadhosain Motejali has said that the giant South Pars gas field provides 70 percent of domestic needs for natural gas, which is the reason behind the importance of pouring money into the development of the field.
title: POGC head calls for investment in South Pars

description: TEHRAN - Yemen’s Ambassador to Tehran Ibrahim Mohammed al-Dailami called for the expansion of energy cooperation between his country and Iran along with the exchange of scientific and technical oil data.
title: Yemen keen on expansion of energy ties with Iran

description: TEHRAN - The National Iranian Oil Refining and Distribution Company (NIORDC) managing director announced on Friday that investment opportunities valued at $19 billion are ready for investors in Iranian refining industries.
title: $19b of investment opportunities up for grabs in Iran’s refining industries

title: Number of exploration drilling rigs to increase fivefold
